Definition: intended to deceive
Example: deceitful advertising; fallacious testimony; smooth, shining, and deceitful as thin ice - S.T.Coleridge; a fraudulent scheme to escape paying taxes
Synonyms: noun, attribute, deceitfulness, fallacious, fraudulent, fraudulence, act, intended, to, deceive, advertising, testimony, smooth, shining, and, as, thin, ice, -, S, T, Coleridge, a, scheme, escape, paying, taxes
Category: adj.all
